We want the $\goldE{\text{total quantity}}$ to be at least $\goldE{300}$ grams. This means we need to rewrite the equation so the $\goldE{\text{total quantity}}$ is isolated:

$\begin{align}
\blueE{\text{Density}}&=\dfrac{\goldE{\text{Total quantity}}}{\maroonD{\text{Volume}}}
\\\\
\blueE{\text{Density}}\cdot\maroonD{\text{Volume}}&=\dfrac{\goldE{\text{Total quantity}}}{\cancel{\maroonD{\text{Volume}}}}\cdot\cancel{\maroonD{\text{Volume}}}
\\\\
\blueE{\text{Density}}\cdot\maroonD{\text{Volume}}&=\goldE{\text{Total quantity}}
\end{align}$

So this is the inequality we want to solve:

$\blueE{\text{Density}}\cdot\maroonD{\text{Volume}}\geq\goldE{300}$

The $\maroonD{\text{volume}}$ of the pyramid-like paperweight is $\dfrac{1}{3}\cdot 100\cdot 6=\maroonD{200}$ cubic centimeters.

Let's denote the density as $\blueE d$.

Now we can plug $\blueE{\text{density}=d}$ and  $\maroonD{\text{volume}=200}$ in the inequality.

$\begin{align}
\blueE{\text{Density}}\cdot\maroonD{\text{Volume}}&\geq\goldE{300}
\\\\
\blueE{d}\cdot\maroonD{200}&\geq\goldE{300}
\\\\
\blueE d&\geq\dfrac{\goldE{300}}{\maroonD{200}}
\\\\
\blueE d&\geq 1.5
\end{align}$

We want the $\maroonD{\text{volume}}$, so let's rewrite the equation so $\maroonD{\text{volume}}$ is isolated:

$\begin{align}
\blueE{\text{Density}}&=\dfrac{\goldE{\text{Total quantity}}}{\maroonD{\text{Volume}}}
\\\\
\blueE{\text{Density}}\cdot\maroonD{\text{Volume}}&=\dfrac{\goldE{\text{Total quantity}}}{\cancel{\maroonD{\text{Volume}}}}\cdot\cancel{\maroonD{\text{Volume}}}
\\\\
\dfrac{\cancel{\blueE{\text{Density}}}\cdot\maroonD{\text{Volume}}}{\cancel{\blueE{\text{Density}}}}&=\dfrac{\goldE{\text{Total quantity}}}{\blueE{\text{Density}}}
\\\\
\maroonD{\text{Volume}}&=\dfrac{\goldE{\text{Total quantity}}}{\blueE{\text{Density}}}
\end{align}$

As mentioned above, the actual $\goldE{\text{total quantity}}$ is $1000-10=\goldE{990}$ grams, since we are trying to find the volume of the filling material within the shell.

Let's denote the ball's radius as $r$. Then, the $\maroonD{\text{volume}}$ is $\maroonD{\dfrac43\pi r^3}$.

Now we can plug $\blueE{\text{density}=1.5}$, $\goldE{\text{total quantity}=990}$, and  $\maroonD{\text{volume}=\dfrac43\pi r^3}$ in the equation.

$\begin{align}
\maroonD{\text{Volume}}&=\dfrac{\goldE{\text{Total quantity}}}{\blueE{\text{Density}}}
\\\\
\maroonD{\dfrac43\pi r^3}&=\dfrac{\goldE{990}}{\blueE{1.5}}
\\\\
r^3&=\dfrac{990}{1.5}\cdot\dfrac34\cdot\dfrac1\pi
\\\\
r^3&=\dfrac{495}{\pi}
\\\\
r&=\sqrt[3]{\dfrac{495}{\pi}}
\\\\
&\approx 5.4
\end{align}$

